1
00:00:12,330 --> 00:00:14,730
We were wondering what was taking so long...

2
00:00:14,730 --> 00:00:17,960
...but now we understand. You were doing this.

3
00:00:20,530 --> 00:00:23,260
Okay. I wanted to surprise you, but....

4
00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:25,190
For your housewarming gift,

5
00:00:25,190 --> 00:00:28,080
I got you a baby chick and a baby duck.

6
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:30,910
Really? You got us a chick and a duck?

7
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:32,210
Oh, great.

8
00:00:32,210 --> 00:00:33,080
Just what you want for

9
00:00:33,080 --> 00:00:36,380
a new house with infants. Bird feces!

10
00:00:37,090 --> 00:00:38,450
But they must've jumped off the table.

11
00:00:38,450 --> 00:00:39,390
Now they're gone!

12
00:00:39,390 --> 00:00:40,620
Don't worry, we'll find them.

13
00:00:40,620 --> 00:00:43,010
Actually, I'm gonna go check on the twins.

14
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:46,270
Oh, God! What did I just step on?

15
00:00:47,310 --> 00:00:49,620
It's okay. It's just an egg roll.

16
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:52,050
You stepped on my egg roll?!

17
00:00:53,550 --> 00:00:54,190
I'm sorry.

18
00:00:54,190 --> 00:00:56,690
I didn't know to look for Chinese food on the floor.

19
00:00:56,690 --> 00:00:58,930
Just put it on a plate and leave.

20
00:01:02,890 --> 00:01:05,930
- Okay. Let's find these birds. - All right.

21
00:01:09,090 --> 00:01:11,730
Wait, wait. You hear that?

22
00:01:14,490 --> 00:01:16,560
They're in the table!

23
00:01:16,940 --> 00:01:19,050
Well, that can't be good.

24
00:01:19,050 --> 00:01:21,420
- We gotta get them out of there! - How?

25
00:01:22,060 --> 00:01:23,940
Maybe we can lure them out. You know any birdcalls?

26
00:01:23,940 --> 00:01:26,650
Oh, tons. I'm quite the woodsman.

27
00:01:27,990 --> 00:01:31,380
Well, maybe we can just tip the table a little.

28
00:01:31,380 --> 00:01:33,740
Joey, wait! The ball!

29
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:51,870
So, what do we do?

30
00:01:51,870 --> 00:01:53,990
Maybe we can open this up somehow.

31
00:01:53,990 --> 00:01:55,340
Okay.

32
00:01:57,220 --> 00:02:00,350
No. It's all glued together.

33
00:02:00,730 --> 00:02:03,800
Does that mean we have to bust it open?

34
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:07,780
- I don't know. Maybe. - Oh, my God.

35
00:02:07,780 --> 00:02:12,110
I know. It's-- It's the foosball table.

36
00:02:14,460 --> 00:02:16,900
All right, you know what? We don't have a choice.

37
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:18,640
It's like I would have said in that sci-fi movie

38
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:20,550
if I'd have gotten the part.

39
00:02:22,130 --> 00:02:25,300
Those are our men in there, and we have to get them out...

40
00:02:26,070 --> 00:02:29,570
...even if I have to sacrifice the most important thing in my life...

41
00:02:29,570 --> 00:02:31,430
...my time machine.

42
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:36,140
- Did that movie ever get made? - It did not.

43
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,300
Ross, where are you going?

44
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:45,570
To talk to Rachel.

45
00:02:45,570 --> 00:02:48,530
Isn't that why we took a ride in the death cab?

46
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:50,470
You're walking up to her at the gate?

47
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:53,010
Have you never chased anyone through the airport before?

48
00:02:53,010 --> 00:02:55,940
Not since my cop show got canceled.

49
00:02:56,850 --> 00:02:59,100
You have to get a ticket to get past security.

50
00:02:59,100 --> 00:03:00,410
What? We're never gonna make it.

51
00:03:00,410 --> 00:03:03,710
Not with that attitude. Now, haul ass!

52
00:03:05,830 --> 00:03:07,620
Okay, if you could all walk slower,

53
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:09,480
that'd be great.

54
00:03:16,740 --> 00:03:20,290
- Madame, your passport, please. - Oh, my God.

55
00:03:20,290 --> 00:03:23,210
I was afraid I wouldn't remember my high school French.

56
00:03:23,210 --> 00:03:26,300
But I understood every word you just said.

57
00:03:26,770 --> 00:03:29,840
- Your boarding pass, please. - Oh, sure.

58
00:03:32,290 --> 00:03:36,200
Shoot, I had it. Oh, I can't believe this.

59
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:37,360
Madame, if you don't have your--

60
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:39,480
I have it, I have it!

61
00:03:41,510 --> 00:03:42,740
Okay, I can't find it,

62
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:46,620
but I remember that I was in seat 32C...

63
00:03:46,620 --> 00:03:49,210
...because that's my bra size.

64
00:03:50,260 --> 00:03:51,560
Madame. You must have your boarding pass--

65
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:52,790
Ok, fine. But you know what?

66
00:03:52,790 --> 00:03:56,440
If I was in 36D, we would not be having this problem.

67
00:04:03,330 --> 00:04:05,660
- Hi. I need a ticket. - Just one?

68
00:04:05,660 --> 00:04:06,810
I drive you here,

69
00:04:06,810 --> 00:04:08,880
and I don't get to see how it works out?

70
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:11,430
Fine. Two tickets. I need two tickets.

71
00:04:11,430 --> 00:04:13,240
We're on our honeymoon.

72
00:04:14,890 --> 00:04:15,870
And the destination?

73
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:18,430
I don't care. Whatever's the cheapest.

74
00:04:18,770 --> 00:04:20,900
I'm so lucky I married you.

75
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:26,700
Oh, shoot. Damn it. Where is it?

76
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:31,480
I found it. I found it. I told you I would find it.

77
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:34,340
In your face. You're a different person.

78
00:04:35,450 --> 00:04:37,120
Sorry.

79
00:04:37,530 --> 00:04:40,950
Okay. Flight 421, Paris.

80
00:04:42,270 --> 00:04:43,570
I don't see it. Do you see it?

81
00:04:43,570 --> 00:04:44,770
No. Did we miss it?

82
00:04:44,780 --> 00:04:48,170
No, no, it's impossible. It doesn't leave for another 20 minutes.

83
00:04:48,290 --> 00:04:50,540
Maybe we have the flight number wrong.

84
00:04:51,140 --> 00:04:52,530
God.

85
00:04:55,270 --> 00:04:57,070
- Hello. - Hey, it's me. Here's Ross.

86
00:04:57,070 --> 00:04:58,380
What?

87
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:00,950
Hey. Hey, listen--

88
00:05:00,950 --> 00:05:04,240
You wouldn't believe the cute noises the twins are making.

89
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,090
Wait, listen.

90
00:05:05,090 --> 00:05:06,590
But Monica--

91
00:05:07,940 --> 00:05:12,690
Monica...

92
00:05:13,350 --> 00:05:14,880
I'm sorry. They were doing it before.

93
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:15,910
That's all right. Listen, listen.

94
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,790
Oh, wait, wait. Here they go again.

95
00:05:18,910 --> 00:05:23,140
Monica...

96
00:05:23,140 --> 00:05:24,640
- <i>Monica?</i> - Isn't that cute?

97
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:27,080
That is precious! Listen....

98
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:30,150
I need Rachel's flight information.

99
00:05:30,150 --> 00:05:31,760
<i>Oh, okay.</i>

100
00:05:31,770 --> 00:05:35,360
All right, it's flight 421. Leaves at 8:40.

101
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:37,450
Yes, that's what I had . It's not on the board.

102
00:05:37,460 --> 00:05:38,200
That's what it says here.

103
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:41,730
Flight 421. Leaves at 8:40. Newark Airport.

104
00:05:41,730 --> 00:05:44,380
- What? - <i>Newark Airport.</i>

105
00:05:44,470 --> 00:05:46,270
Why? Where are you?

106
00:05:47,260 --> 00:05:48,860
JFK.

107
00:06:18,290 --> 00:06:19,550
Don't worry, you guys!

108
00:06:19,550 --> 00:06:21,750
We're gonna get you out of there!

109
00:06:22,890 --> 00:06:26,730
And we're also gonna buy you tiny bird hearing aids.

110
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:35,300
Okay. Here goes.

111
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:41,750
What's the matter?

112
00:06:42,740 --> 00:06:46,040
I need to say goodbye to the table first.

113
00:06:47,690 --> 00:06:49,210
I understand.

114
00:06:50,470 --> 00:06:51,830
Okay.

115
00:06:55,410 --> 00:06:56,830
Table...

116
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:04,010
...you have given us so many great times.

117
00:07:04,510 --> 00:07:10,780
And you guys, Jordan, Victor, Joel....

118
00:07:11,620 --> 00:07:14,260
All of you guys. What can I say?

119
00:07:15,130 --> 00:07:20,610
You guys make us look good.

120
00:07:23,970 --> 00:07:26,550
- You want to say anything? - I don't know.

121
00:07:28,410 --> 00:07:32,420
Except that, for one last time....

122
00:07:33,340 --> 00:07:37,950
Good game...

123
00:07:40,110 --> 00:07:41,560
Good game.

124
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,810
Okay. Here we go.

125
00:07:55,340 --> 00:07:56,980
I can't do it.

126
00:07:57,930 --> 00:07:59,880
Well, I can't do it either.

127
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:01,770
Hey. Did you find them?

128
00:08:01,770 --> 00:08:03,920
Yeah. They're stuck inside the table.

129
00:08:03,930 --> 00:08:06,740
And we have to bust it open, but neither of us can do it.

130
00:08:06,740 --> 00:08:11,540
Oh, well, sure. It's got to be so hard.

131
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,020
I'll do it. Give me.

132
00:08:19,370 --> 00:08:20,930
Phoebe!

133
00:08:21,220 --> 00:08:22,910
No, no, no!

134
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:27,340
Wow, I've never gone this fast before.

135
00:08:27,610 --> 00:08:29,010
Phoebe, forget it, okay?

136
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:31,040
Newark is, like, an hour away.

137
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,780
There's no way we'll make it in time.

138
00:08:32,780 --> 00:08:34,740
She's got her cell. You could call her.

139
00:08:34,740 --> 00:08:36,710
I am not doing this over the phone.

140
00:08:36,710 --> 00:08:39,140
You don't have any other choice.

141
00:08:46,010 --> 00:08:48,140
- Hello? - Rachel. Oh, good.

142
00:08:48,140 --> 00:08:50,270
By the way, did you just get on the plane?

143
00:08:50,270 --> 00:08:52,490
- Yeah. - For what is worse, we would have caught her...

144
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:54,400
...if we were at the right airport.

145
00:08:56,640 --> 00:09:01,090
- Rachel, hang on. - <i>No. No. No.</i>

146
00:09:01,090 --> 00:09:03,270
Phoebe, is everything okay?

147
00:09:05,300 --> 00:09:09,940
Actually, no. No. You have to get off the plane.

148
00:09:09,950 --> 00:09:12,280
- What? Why? - I have this feeling that...

149
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:13,630
...something's wrong with it.

150
00:09:13,630 --> 00:09:18,270
Something is wrong with the left phalange.

151
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:23,020
Oh, honey, I'm sure there's nothing wrong with the plane.

152
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:24,070
Look, I have to go.

153
00:09:24,070 --> 00:09:27,980
I love you, and l will call you the minute I get to Paris.

154
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:32,010
What was that?

155
00:09:32,010 --> 00:09:34,320
Oh, that was just my crazy friend.

156
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:35,850
She told me to get off the plane

157
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:37,940
because she had a "feeling" that there...

158
00:09:37,940 --> 00:09:41,440
...was something wrong with the left phalange.

159
00:09:42,370 --> 00:09:44,890
Okay. That doesn't sound good.

160
00:09:45,050 --> 00:09:46,040
Oh, I wouldn't worry about it.

161
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:47,420
She comes up with this stuff,

162
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:48,870
and she's almost never right.

163
00:09:48,870 --> 00:09:50,840
But she is sometimes.

164
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,200
Well....

165
00:09:54,060 --> 00:09:54,920
What are you doing?

166
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:56,300
I can't take this plane now.

167
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:58,050
Excuse me, sir. Where are you going?

168
00:09:58,050 --> 00:09:59,640
I have to get off this plane.

169
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:02,050
Her friend has a feeling

170
00:10:02,050 --> 00:10:04,750
something's wrong with the left phalange.

171
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:10,580
Could I get some peanuts?

172
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:12,460
What's wrong with the plane?

173
00:10:12,460 --> 00:10:14,790
There's nothing wrong.

174
00:10:14,790 --> 00:10:15,900
The left phalange.

175
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:17,720
There's no "phalange."

176
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:21,020
Oh, my God. This plane doesn't even have a phalange.

177
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:23,900
- I'm not flying on it. - Ma'am. Please sit down.

178
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:24,990
What's going on?

179
00:10:24,990 --> 00:10:28,330
We're getting off. There is no phalange!

180
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:35,160
This is ridiculous. I--

181
00:10:37,170 --> 00:10:38,680
Yeah, okay.

182
00:10:47,590 --> 00:10:50,330
All right. My job here is done.

183
00:10:51,420 --> 00:10:54,120
That was impressive.

184
00:10:55,310 --> 00:10:57,860
Yeah. You didn't even use the tools for most of it.

185
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,100
Yeah, they were just slowing me down.

186
00:11:01,320 --> 00:11:03,940
All right. I gotta get back to the babies.

187
00:11:03,940 --> 00:11:05,730
See you girls later.

188
00:11:09,660 --> 00:11:12,980
- Sorry about the table, man. - Yeah.

189
00:11:13,530 --> 00:11:15,140
You gonna buy a new one?

190
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:18,940
Probably not. No.

191
00:11:18,940 --> 00:11:20,360
I don't know how much I'm gonna want to play

192
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:21,840
after you go.

193
00:11:25,300 --> 00:11:28,480
- At least we got these little guys out. - Yeah.

194
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:31,140
We were worried about you.

195
00:11:35,670 --> 00:11:37,260
I guess I better get used to things

196
00:11:37,260 --> 00:11:39,490
crapping in my hand, huh?

197
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:50,890
I'm gonna miss these little guys.

198
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:53,310
It was nice having birds around again.

199
00:11:54,730 --> 00:11:56,230
Hey, you know what?

200
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:58,620
Maybe we should keep them here with you.

201
00:11:58,950 --> 00:11:59,780
What?

202
00:11:59,780 --> 00:12:02,050
Yeah. We got a lot going on right now.

203
00:12:02,050 --> 00:12:04,730
And plus, here, they'd have their own room.

204
00:12:06,180 --> 00:12:08,180
I could get a goose!

205
00:12:10,060 --> 00:12:13,420
You know, I think you're set with the poultry.

206
00:12:16,130 --> 00:12:18,410
Thanks, man. You hear that, you guys?

207
00:12:18,410 --> 00:12:19,880
You're gonna get to stay here.

208
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:22,540
And it's good...

209
00:12:22,610 --> 00:12:24,150
...you know, because....

210
00:12:25,630 --> 00:12:26,550
Because now you have a reason

211
00:12:26,550 --> 00:12:28,270
to come visit.

212
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:33,970
I think there may be another reason.

213
00:12:42,210 --> 00:12:43,620
So....

214
00:12:45,830 --> 00:12:50,460
Awkward hug or lame cool-guy handshake?

215
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:52,760
Yeah, well, you know,

216
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:55,000
lame cool-guy handshake.

217
00:13:13,420 --> 00:13:16,060
Ma'am, I assure you, the plane is fine.

218
00:13:16,060 --> 00:13:18,430
And you fixed the phalange?

219
00:13:19,660 --> 00:13:21,910
Yes. The phalange's fixed.

220
00:13:21,910 --> 00:13:22,430
As a matter of fact,

221
00:13:22,430 --> 00:13:24,270
we've put a whole lot of extra phalanges onboard,

222
00:13:24,270 --> 00:13:25,800
just in case.

223
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:33,100
- Where is she? - I don't see her.

224
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:35,830
- Rachel! Rachel Green! - There she is!

225
00:13:35,830 --> 00:13:38,670
Rachel! Rachel!

226
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:40,890
Whoa, do you have a boarding pass?

227
00:13:40,890 --> 00:13:42,450
No. I just have to talk to someone.

228
00:13:42,450 --> 00:13:44,670
I'm sorry. You need a boarding pass.

229
00:13:44,670 --> 00:13:48,990
- No, no. But you don't-- - Rachel!

230
00:13:51,450 --> 00:13:52,040
What? Oh, my God.

231
00:13:52,050 --> 00:13:54,300
What are you guys doing here?

232
00:13:54,590 --> 00:13:56,450
Okay. You're on.

233
00:13:56,450 --> 00:13:57,710
What? What, Ross?

234
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:59,850
Okay, you're scaring me. What's going on?

235
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:03,340
- Okay. Thing is.... - Yeah.

236
00:14:03,930 --> 00:14:06,300
- Don't go. - What?

237
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:07,840
Please, please stay with me.

238
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:11,550
I am so in love with you. Please don't go.

239
00:14:12,590 --> 00:14:14,650
- Oh, my God. - I know. I know.

240
00:14:14,650 --> 00:14:16,650
I shouldn't have waited till now to say it,

241
00:14:16,650 --> 00:14:19,700
but-- That was stupid, okay? I'm sorry.

242
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:21,600
But I'm telling you now.

243
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,130
I love you.

244
00:14:23,820 --> 00:14:26,060
Do not get on this plane.

245
00:14:26,570 --> 00:14:29,290
Miss, are you boarding the plane?

246
00:14:29,380 --> 00:14:30,780
Hey, hey.

247
00:14:31,560 --> 00:14:35,530
I know you love me. I know you do.

248
00:14:36,530 --> 00:14:38,280
- Miss. - I....

249
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:41,100
l.... I have to get on the plane.

250
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:42,700
- No, you don't. - Yes, I do.

251
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:45,260
- No, you don't. I do. - They're waiting for me, Ross.

252
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:46,380
I can't do this right now,

253
00:14:46,380 --> 00:14:49,110
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

254
00:14:49,110 --> 00:14:50,510
Rachel.

255
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:53,150
I'm so sorry.

256
00:15:08,580 --> 00:15:10,130
I really thought she'd stay.

257
00:15:10,130 --> 00:15:11,640
I know.

258
00:15:12,530 --> 00:15:13,980
I'm sorry.

259
00:15:27,650 --> 00:15:30,840
Well, that's it.

260
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:32,810
Everything's packed.

261
00:15:36,490 --> 00:15:38,070
This is weird.

262
00:15:38,190 --> 00:15:39,020
I know.

263
00:15:39,020 --> 00:15:40,370
Yeah.

264
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:43,740
Does this mean there's nothing to eat?

265
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:48,130
I put three lasagnas in your freezer.

266
00:15:49,190 --> 00:15:50,770
I love you.

267
00:15:54,530 --> 00:15:55,390
Hey.

268
00:15:55,390 --> 00:15:57,160
Hey. Did you guys make it in time?

269
00:15:57,160 --> 00:15:57,870
Yeah, yeah.

270
00:15:57,870 --> 00:16:01,440
He talked to her, but she got on the plane anyway.

271
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:05,300
Where's Ross?

272
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:07,730
He went home. He didn't want to see anybody.

273
00:16:25,470 --> 00:16:28,990
<i>Ross. Hi, it's me.</i>

274
00:16:29,590 --> 00:16:31,790
<i>I just got back on the plane,</i>

275
00:16:31,790 --> 00:16:34,060
<i>and I just feel awful.</i>

276
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:36,650
<i>That is so not how I wanted</i>

277
00:16:36,650 --> 00:16:38,710
<i>things to end with us.</i>

278
00:16:40,110 --> 00:16:42,660
<i>It's just that I wasn't expecting</i>

279
00:16:42,660 --> 00:16:43,360
<i>to see you.</i>

280
00:16:43,370 --> 00:16:45,250
<i>And all of a sudden you're there</i>

281
00:16:45,250 --> 00:16:47,690
<i>and saying these things.</i>

282
00:16:48,310 --> 00:16:49,880
<i>Now I'm just sitting here</i>

283
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:51,500
<i>and thinking...</i>

284
00:16:51,530 --> 00:16:53,310
<i>...of all the stuff I should have said</i>

285
00:16:53,310 --> 00:16:54,990
<i>and I didn't.</i>

286
00:16:55,510 --> 00:16:57,020
<i>I mean, I didn't even get to tell you</i>

287
00:16:57,020 --> 00:16:58,970
<i>that I love you too.</i>

288
00:17:00,180 --> 00:17:04,150
<i>Because of course I do. I love you.</i>

289
00:17:05,490 --> 00:17:07,000
<i>I love you.</i>

290
00:17:08,170 --> 00:17:09,700
<i>I love you.</i>

291
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:14,460
<i>What am I doing? I love you.</i>

292
00:17:17,170 --> 00:17:18,790
<i>I've got to see you.</i>

293
00:17:18,790 --> 00:17:20,230
<i>I've got to get off this plane.</i>

294
00:17:20,230 --> 00:17:21,670
Oh, my God.

295
00:17:22,840 --> 00:17:24,110
<i>Okay, excuse me.</i>

296
00:17:24,110 --> 00:17:25,380
<i>Miss, please sit down.</i>

297
00:17:25,380 --> 00:17:27,540
<i>No, I'm sorry. I'm really sorry,</i>

298
00:17:27,540 --> 00:17:28,730
<i>but I need to get off the plane.</i>

299
00:17:28,730 --> 00:17:30,260
<i>I need to tell someone that I love them.</i>

300
00:17:30,260 --> 00:17:31,960
<i>Miss, I can't let you off.</i>

301
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:34,030
Let her off the plane!

302
00:17:35,710 --> 00:17:37,650
<i>I am afraid you are gonna have to take a seat.</i>

303
00:17:37,660 --> 00:17:40,010
<i>Oh, please, Miss.</i> <i>You don't understand.</i>

304
00:17:40,010 --> 00:17:42,120
Try to understand!

305
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:44,790
<i>Come on, miss, isn't there any way</i>

306
00:17:44,790 --> 00:17:47,010
<i>that you can just let me off the</i>--<i>?</i>

307
00:17:47,010 --> 00:17:48,690
No! No!

308
00:17:49,770 --> 00:17:51,950
Oh, my God. Did she get off the plane?

309
00:17:51,950 --> 00:17:53,890
Did she get off the plane?

310
00:17:55,780 --> 00:17:57,850
I got off the plane.

311
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:10,340
You got off the plane.

312
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:24,560
I do love you.

313
00:18:25,220 --> 00:18:26,050
I love you too,

314
00:18:26,050 --> 00:18:28,160
and I am never letting you go again.

315
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:30,340
Okay. Because this is where I want to be.

316
00:18:30,340 --> 00:18:31,670
No more messing around.

317
00:18:31,670 --> 00:18:33,020
I don't want to mess this up again.

318
00:18:33,020 --> 00:18:36,260
Me neither. We're done being stupid.

319
00:18:36,270 --> 00:18:39,000
Okay. It's you and me, all right? This is it.

320
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:42,220
This is it. Unless we're on a break.

321
00:18:52,360 --> 00:18:54,870
Don't make jokes now.

322
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:15,780
Okay, please be careful with that.

323
00:19:15,780 --> 00:19:18,260
It was my grandmother's. Be careful.

324
00:19:18,260 --> 00:19:19,660
Thank you.

325
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:21,120
If that falls off the truck,

326
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:23,400
it wouldn't be the worst thing.

327
00:19:35,450 --> 00:19:36,960
I know.

328
00:19:37,130 --> 00:19:39,630
Seems smaller somehow.

329
00:19:41,450 --> 00:19:44,590
Has it always been purple?

330
00:19:47,490 --> 00:19:49,560
Look around, you guys.

331
00:19:49,610 --> 00:19:51,770
This was your first home.

332
00:19:52,860 --> 00:19:55,160
And it was a happy place,

333
00:19:55,330 --> 00:19:58,650
filled with love and laughter.

334
00:19:59,070 --> 00:20:00,040
But more important,

335
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:03,470
because of rent control, it was a frigging steal.

336
00:20:07,710 --> 00:20:10,520
Hey, do you realize that, at one time or another,

337
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:13,110
we all lived in this apartment?

338
00:20:13,340 --> 00:20:15,260
Oh, yeah. That's true.

339
00:20:15,260 --> 00:20:17,270
I haven't.

340
00:20:18,910 --> 00:20:20,730
What about that summer during college

341
00:20:20,730 --> 00:20:22,180
that you lived with Grandma...

342
00:20:22,180 --> 00:20:24,620
...and you tried to make it as a dancer?

343
00:20:29,730 --> 00:20:31,980
Do you realize we almost made it 10 years

344
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:33,950
without that coming up?

345
00:20:37,650 --> 00:20:39,290
Oh, honey, I forgot.

346
00:20:39,290 --> 00:20:41,250
I promised Treeger that we'd leave our keys.

347
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:42,770
Oh, okay.

348
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:20,470
- So I guess this is it. - Yeah.

349
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:23,890
I guess so.

350
00:21:25,980 --> 00:21:28,370
This is harder than I thought it would be.

351
00:21:28,580 --> 00:21:30,560
Oh, it's gonna be okay.

352
00:21:33,810 --> 00:21:35,180
Come on.

353
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:44,080
Do you guys have to go to the new house now,

354
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:46,320
or do you have some time?

355
00:21:49,590 --> 00:21:51,280
We got some time.

356
00:21:51,460 --> 00:21:55,080
- Okay. Should we get some coffee? - Sure.

357
00:21:56,600 --> 00:21:58,060
Where?

